File: The trial of three suspects accused in the killing Sindiso Magaqa is expected to start in the Scottburgh Magistrate's Court. JOHANNESBURG - The trial of three suspects accused in the killing Sindiso Magaqa is expected to start in the Scottburgh Magistrate's Court on Monday. The former ANC Youth League secretary-general was gunned down in KwaZulu-Natal in 2017. Sibonelo Myeza, Mbulelo Mpofana and Mxolisi Ncalane are facing murder charges. They were denied bail earlier this year. WATCH: Sindiso Magaqa's friend slams ANC The State provisionally dropped charges against the former mayor who’s now deputy KZN Legislature speaker, Mluleki Ndobe. Whistleblower and Magaqa's friend Thabani Zulu says he won't attend the trial due to safety concerns. Zulu testified during a probe into political killings in KZN and exposed rampant corruption at Umzimkhulu Municipality where Magaqa was a councillor. The trial is set for 20 days.